com.googlecode.streamflyer.experimental.range2

Class MatchResultShifted

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.streamflyer.experimental.range2.MatchResultShifted
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MatchResult

    public class MatchResultShifted
extends Object
implements MatchResult
    This MatchResult is useful if another match result is no longer valid because the input for the match result has been shifted either to the begin or to the end of the input. This can happen if the input was a modifiable CharSequence like StringBuilder and in this character sequence some characters are deleted or inserted before the match.
    Since:
    1.1.0
    Author:
    rwoo
